The paper discusses online convex optimization algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of regularization and mirror descent methods suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The analysis of implicit updates and the focus on regret bounds suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of optimization techniques and the analysis of large datasets suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Finally, the focus on theoretical analysis and algorithmic design suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
